# Cursor workspace folder is mostly local-only operator state, but we DO
# track the project's dev-flow skill (SKILL.md + scripts) so anyone
# checking out the repo gets the same dev tooling. Anything else under
# .cursor/ stays ignored by default — including the worktree's own
# mcp.json, which carries machine-specific paths and may carry secrets in
# env vars.
.cursor/*
!.cursor/skills/
.cursor/skills/*
!.cursor/skills/mithwire-mcp-dev-flow/

*.log
/results
uv.lock